Siya Mlambo was taken during what was reported to be a robbery in Protea Glen on Tuesday night. JOHANNESBURG - Police are looking for a fourth suspect in connection with the kidnapping of a 14-month-old toddler from a home in Soweto.Siya Mlambo was taken during what was reported to be a robbery in Protea Glen on Tuesday night.He was found unharmed in Newcastle yesterday and his nanny and two men have been arrested.Police spokesperson Fred Kekana says, The two suspects are cousins to the lady that we have arrested. We are still looking for once suspect who is still on the run. We know who he is. (Edited by Neo Koza)